e non-universality of the IMF in ETGs may be confined to their\ncore regions, and points towards a picture in which the stars in these central\nregions may have formed in fundamentally different physical conditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Nov 2017 21:22:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-27"}
